{"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/TUIkit\/documentation\/TUIkit"]]},"sections":[],"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"anchor":"Overview","type":"heading","text":"Overview","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"TUIkit uses a layered event dispatch system. When a key is pressed, it passes through up to five layers. The first layer that consumes the event wins: remaining layers are skipped. Layer 0 (text input) and Layer 3 (focus system) are mutually exclusive: when a text input element is focused, Layer 0 runs and Layer 3 is skipped."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"keyboard-event-dispatch.png"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Additionally, "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Ctrl+C"},{"type":"text","text":" (SIGINT) is handled at the OS signal level "},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"before"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":" any of these layers: it always terminates the application."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"Available-Keys","type":"heading","text":"Available Keys","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"code":"Key","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" enum defines all keys that TUIkit can recognize from terminal input:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"Character-Keys","type":"heading","text":"Character Keys","level":3},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Any printable character is represented as "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".character(Character)"},{"type":"text","text":":"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","code":[".onKeyPress(Key.from(\"x\")) {","    \/\/ handle \"x\" key","}"],"syntax":"swift"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Uppercase detection: when a capital letter is typed, the resulting "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"KeyEvent"},{"type":"text","text":" has "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"shift: true"},{"type":"text","text":" set automatically."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"Special-Keys","type":"headin